we use cli to automated tasks and automated repaeated tasks so we don;t need to present there manually

download aws cli to access all aws commands use

    curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
    unzip awscliv2.zip
    sudo ./aws/install

now go on iam user and create a secret key for the console login to sign in console
use

aws configure

aws iam list-users -> use this command to get access of the allusers

best practises ->
1->Avoid using root account expect of account setup
2->add users to a group and assigns permissions to a group
3->use password policy or MFA
4->USe Access Keys for Cli/SDK
5->don;t share access key or password
6->Audit the permissions using iam credintials report

https://415407092979.signin.aws.amazon.com/console use this link to login to console
